The paper focuses on developing a smart system for mechanical assembly using multi-modal vision and AI planning, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper specifically discusses the use of 3D visual detection and point cloud matching, which are common techniques in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of AI planning also suggests that the paper may fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implementation of the developed approaches on industrial robots, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
